
- Implement a feedback loop that make sure the motor has a certain
  position within certain bounds.  (One can also give up after too
  many tries, for example if the bounds are too tight.)

- Measure the distance to the walls by taking the min of the distances
  measured with a, say, 10 degree variation around the wanted direction.


- Read the papers
  http://www.case.edu/artsci/math/alexander/pubs.html#wmr
